cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with identifying influential nodes in a network and its effect on information diffusion and virus spreading. It also mentions the importance of community structure in real-world networks, which is a key aspect of social networks. 

It could also belong to cs.SD (Software Development and Programming) as it proposes a new measure for centrality in modular networks. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible sub-category as the paper discusses the dynamics of networks and the effect of community structure on it. 

cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with network topology and its impact on information diffusion. 

Finally, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible sub-category as the paper proposes a new algorithm for identifying influential nodes in modular networks.
